<cell id="md-cell-06"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type>## Cell 6 — Restore Previous Results from Drive

Copy any previously saved CSV result files from /content/drive/MyDrive/research back into the results directory, enabling resumption of an interrupted run.</cell id="md-cell-06">
<cell id="code-cell-06"># Run cells in order -- this is Cell 6 of 13
import shutil, os

DRIVE_DIR = '/content/drive/MyDrive/research'
RESULTS_DIR = '/content/ADVC/results'

files = [
    'phase1_results.csv',
    'phase2_at_results.csv',
    'phase2_atkd_results.csv',
    'phase3_results.csv',
]

restored = []
for f in files:
    src = os.path.join(DRIVE_DIR, f)
    dst = os.path.join(RESULTS_DIR, f)
    if os.path.exists(src):
        shutil.copy(src, dst)
        restored.append(f)
        print('Restored: ' + f)
    else:
        print('Not found on Drive (first run or not yet created): ' + f)

print()
if restored:
    print(str(len(restored)) + ' file(s) restored from ' + DRIVE_DIR)
else:
    print('No previous results found -- starting fresh.')</cell id="code-cell-06">
<cell id="md-cell-07"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type>## Cell 7 — Upload Phase 1 Results

Open a file picker to manually upload your phase1_results.csv from your local machine and save it to the results directory.</cell id="md-cell-07">
<cell id="code-cell-07"># Run cells in order -- this is Cell 7 of 13
import shutil, os
from google.colab import files

RESULTS_DIR = '/content/ADVC/results'
DRIVE_DIR = '/content/drive/MyDrive/research'

print('Select your phase1_results.csv when the file picker appears ...')
uploaded = files.upload()

if 'phase1_results.csv' in uploaded:
    dst = os.path.join(RESULTS_DIR, 'phase1_results.csv')
    with open(dst, 'wb') as fh:
        fh.write(uploaded['phase1_results.csv'])
    print('Saved to ' + dst)
    os.makedirs(DRIVE_DIR, exist_ok=True)
    shutil.copy(dst, os.path.join(DRIVE_DIR, 'phase1_results.csv'))
    print('Also backed up to Drive: ' + DRIVE_DIR)
else:
    uploaded_names = list(uploaded.keys())
    if uploaded_names:
        print('WARNING: expected phase1_results.csv but got ' + str(uploaded_names))
        print('Rename your file to phase1_results.csv and re-run this cell.')
    else:
        print('No file was uploaded. Re-run this cell to try again.')</cell id="code-cell-07">
<cell id="f00a3f7c"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type>## Cell 7b — Set ImageNet Data Paths

Point `configs/base.yaml` at your ImageNet directory before running any experiment. The cell writes the absolute paths into the config so the experiment scripts find `val/` and `train/` correctly regardless of which Drive account is mounted.</cell id="f00a3f7c">
<cell id="2d9aa5ab"># Run cells in order -- this is Cell 7b of 13
# Set IMAGENET_DIR to the folder that contains your val/ and train/ subdirectories.
# Default assumes ImageNet is on your Drive at MyDrive/research/data/imagenet.
# Change the path below if yours is stored elsewhere.
import yaml, os

IMAGENET_DIR = '/content/drive/MyDrive/research/data/imagenet'

CONFIG_PATH = '/content/ADVC/configs/base.yaml'

with open(CONFIG_PATH) as f:
    cfg = yaml.safe_load(f)

cfg['dataset']['val_dir']   = os.path.join(IMAGENET_DIR, 'val')
cfg['dataset']['train_dir'] = os.path.join(IMAGENET_DIR, 'train')

with open(CONFIG_PATH, 'w') as f:
    yaml.dump(cfg, f, default_flow_style=False, sort_keys=False)

print('configs/base.yaml updated:')
print('  val_dir  : ' + cfg['dataset']['val_dir'])
print('  train_dir: ' + cfg['dataset']['train_dir'])
print()

ok = True
for label, path in [('val', cfg['dataset']['val_dir']), ('train', cfg['dataset']['train_dir'])]:
    if os.path.isdir(path):
        n = len(os.listdir(path))
        print('  OK  ' + label + '/ found  (' + str(n) + ' entries)')
    else:
        print('  MISSING  ' + path)
        print('  Mount Drive and confirm ImageNet is at ' + IMAGENET_DIR)
        ok = False

if ok:
    print()
    print('Data paths verified. Ready to copy to local disk (Cell 7c).')</cell id="2d9aa5ab">
<cell id="md-cell-7c"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type>## Cell 7c — Copy Dataset from Drive to Local NVMe

Reading images directly from Google Drive is ~100x slower than local disk.
This cell copies the ImageNet subset from Drive to the Colab VM's local NVMe once per session.
The copy takes ~2 minutes and must complete before running any experiment cell.
After copying, configs/base.yaml is updated to point at the local path.</cell id="md-cell-7c">
<cell id="code-cell-7c"># Run cells in order -- this is Cell 7c of 13
import shutil, os, yaml

DRIVE_DATA  = '/content/drive/MyDrive/research/data/imagenet'
LOCAL_DATA  = '/content/ADVC/data/imagenet'
CONFIG_PATH = '/content/ADVC/configs/base.yaml'

if not os.path.exists(LOCAL_DATA):
    print('Copying dataset from Drive to local NVMe — this takes ~2 min ...')
    shutil.copytree(DRIVE_DATA, LOCAL_DATA)
    print('Copy complete. Dataset is now on local disk.')
else:
    print('Dataset already on local disk — skipping copy.')

# Update config to point at local paths so experiment scripts read from NVMe.
with open(CONFIG_PATH) as f:
    cfg = yaml.safe_load(f)

cfg['dataset']['val_dir']   = LOCAL_DATA + '/val'
cfg['dataset']['train_dir'] = LOCAL_DATA + '/train'

with open(CONFIG_PATH, 'w') as f:
    yaml.dump(cfg, f, default_flow_style=False, sort_keys=False)

print()
print('configs/base.yaml updated to local paths:')
print('  val_dir  : ' + cfg['dataset']['val_dir'])
print('  train_dir: ' + cfg['dataset']['train_dir'])

ok = True
for label, path in [('val', cfg['dataset']['val_dir']), ('train', cfg['dataset']['train_dir'])]:
    if os.path.isdir(path):
        n = len(os.listdir(path))
        print('  OK  ' + label + '/ found  (' + str(n) + ' entries)')
    else:
        print('  MISSING  ' + path)
        ok = False

if ok:
    print()
    print('Local data ready. Proceed to Cell 8.')</cell id="code-cell-7c">
<cell id="md-cell-08"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type>## Cell 8 — Run Phase 2a: Adversarial Training (AT) Defense

Run eval_phase2_at.py via subprocess with live output streaming. After the script completes, phase2_at_results.csv is immediately backed up to Drive.</cell id="md-cell-08">
<cell id="code-cell-08"># Run cells in order -- this is Cell 8 of 13
import subprocess, sys, shutil, os

ADVC_DIR = '/content/ADVC'
DRIVE_DIR = '/content/drive/MyDrive/research'
SCRIPT = os.path.join(ADVC_DIR, 'experiments', 'eval_phase2_at.py')
RESULTS_FILE = os.path.join(ADVC_DIR, 'results', 'phase2_at_results.csv')

print('=' * 60)
print('Phase 2a: AT defense sweep')
print('=' * 60)

proc = subprocess.Popen(
    [sys.executable, SCRIPT],
    stdout=subprocess.PIPE,
    stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,
    text=True,
    bufsize=1,
    cwd=ADVC_DIR,
)

for line in proc.stdout:
    print(line, end='', flush=True)

proc.wait()
print()
print('[Cell 8] Process exited with return code ' + str(proc.returncode))

os.makedirs(DRIVE_DIR, exist_ok=True)
if os.path.exists(RESULTS_FILE):
    shutil.copy(RESULTS_FILE, os.path.join(DRIVE_DIR, 'phase2_at_results.csv'))
    print('[Cell 8] phase2_at_results.csv backed up to ' + DRIVE_DIR)
else:
    print('[Cell 8] WARNING: phase2_at_results.csv not found -- check run output above.')</cell id="code-cell-08">
